verses.verse: To the chief<WH5329> Musician,<WH5329> A Song<WH7892> or Psalm.<WH4210> Make a joyful noise to God,<WH430> all<WH3605> you lands:<WH776>
Sing<WH2167> forth the honor<WH3519> of his name:<WH8034> make<WH7760> his praise<WH8416> glorious.<WH3519>
Say<WH559> to God,<WH430> How<WH4100> terrible<WH3372> are you in your works!<WH4639> through the greatness<WH7230> of your power<WH5797> shall your enemies<WH341> submit<WH3584> themselves to you.
All<WH3605> the earth<WH776> shall worship<WH7812> you, and shall sing<WH2167> to you; they shall sing<WH2167> to your name.<WH8034> Selah.<WH5542>
Come<WH3212> and see<WH7200> the works<WH4659> of God:<WH430> he is terrible<WH3372> in his doing<WH5949> toward<WH5921> the children<WH1121> of men.<WH120>
He turned<WH2015> the sea<WH3220> into dry<WH3004> land:<WH776> they went<WH5674> through the flood<WH5104> on foot:<WH7272> there<WH8033> did we rejoice<WH8055> in him.
He rules<WH4910> by his power<WH1369> for ever;<WH5769> his eyes<WH5869> behold<WH6822> the nations:<WH1471> let not the rebellious<WH5637> exalt<WH7311> themselves. Selah.<WH5542>
O bless<WH1288> our God,<WH430> you people,<WH5971> and make the voice<WH6963> of his praise<WH8416> to be heard:<WH8085>
Which holds<WH7760> our soul<WH5315> in life,<WH2416> and suffers<WH5414> not our feet<WH7272> to be moved.<WH4132>
For you, O God,<WH430> have proved<WH974> us: you have tried<WH6884> us, as silver<WH3701> is tried.<WH6884>
You brought<WH935> us into the net;<WH4685> you laid<WH7760> affliction<WH4157> on our loins.<WH4975>
You have caused men<WH582> to ride<WH7392> over our heads;<WH7218> we went<WH935> through fire<WH784> and through water:<WH4325> but you brought<WH3318> us out into a wealthy<WH7310> place.
I will go<WH935> into your house<WH1004> with burnt<WH5930> offerings: I will pay<WH7999> you my vows,<WH5088>
Which<WH834> my lips<WH8193> have uttered,<WH6475> and my mouth<WH6310> has spoken,<WH1696> when I was in trouble.<WH6862>
I will offer<WH5927> to you burnt<WH5930> sacrifices of fatted calves,<WH4220> with the incense<WH7004> of rams;<WH352> I will offer<WH6213> bullocks<WH1241> with goats.<WH6260> Selah.<WH5542>
Come<WH3212> and hear,<WH8085> all<WH3605> you that fear<WH3373> God,<WH430> and I will declare<WH5608> what<WH834> he has done<WH6213> for my soul.<WH5315>
I cried<WH7121> to him with my mouth,<WH6310> and he was extolled<WH7318> with my tongue.<WH3956>
If<WH518> I regard<WH7200> iniquity<WH205> in my heart,<WH3820> the Lord<WH136> will not hear<WH8085> me:
But truly<WH403> God<WH430> has heard<WH8085> me; he has attended<WH7181> to the voice<WH6963> of my prayer.<WH8605>
Blessed<WH1288> be God,<WH430> which<WH834> has not turned<WH5493> away my prayer,<WH8605> nor his mercy<WH2617> from me.
